description: Also issued by Pierre Chevalier; see privilege, p. [16] of preliminaries. T.p. engraving of the French royal arms. Eleven engraved ill., including ports. of Christophe de Thou (1508-1582), p. 347; Bon Broué (d. 1588), p. [561], signed by Thomas de Leu; Jean-Papir Masson (1544-1611), signed by L. Gaultier, p. 983. Ill. on p. 766 signed by Du Brayet. Woodcut head- and tail-pieces, initials. Signatures: ã e A-8E. Includes index. Sloan candidate. Binding: old sheepskin. Spine tooled in gilt, including title on red label. Page edges red. Green silk place marker
